01/06/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The justice ministry has prepared draft changes to the Penal Code, aimed at preventing the distribution of stolen goods.
At a news conference Wednesday (31 May), Justice Minister Aldo Bumci said the draft adjustments envision stricter sanctions for those who purchase or use stolen merchandise.
Sentences of three months to six years in prison and fines of 853 euros would be imposed, he added.
(Albanian News - 01/06/06)
